* Clone into ~/.vim: `git clone git@github.com:fvisin/vim.git ~/.vim`

* Run:
    ```
    git submodule update --init --recursive
    *** at lisa
        cd
        
        # NON FUNZIONA...
        hg clone https://vim.googlecode.com/hg/ vim
        cd vim/src
        CPPFLAGS="`python-config --cflags`" LDFLAGS="`python-config --ldflags`" ./configure --prefix=$HOME/.local_extra --with-features=huge --disable-gui --enable-pythoninterp --with-python-config-dir=/u/lisa/local/install_package.fc14_v3/Canopy1.4/appdata/canopy-1.4.0.1938.rh5-x86_64/lib/python2.7/config
        make && make install

        cd
        wget http://www.cmake.org/files/v3.2/cmake-3.2.2.tar.gz
        tar -zxvf cmake-3.2.2.tar.gz
        cd cmake-3.2.2
        ./configure --prefix=$HOME/.local_extra
        make && make install

        cd $HOME/.vim/bundle/YouCompleteMe
        ./install.sh --system-boost
    *** else
        ./install.sh
    ***
    ```

* Install python flake8 or any other syntax checker allowed by syntastic

* (Install jedi: `pip install jedi` --> not anymore)

* Copy vimrc or vimrc_lisa in ~/.vimrc

* Read the vimrc docstring to learn about the shortcuts keys of the tools
